{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01R3yApFFtJdTWvVzAmd7V1H","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear: the health check on `mongodb-replica-1` is failing with \"SCRAM authentication failed, storedKey mismatch\" for the `health-user`. This means the password stored in the `health-user-password` secret doesn't match what's stored in MongoDB on this pod.\n\nLet me look at the resources - the health-user-password secret, the health-check script, and any configmaps/overrides to understand the full picture.\n\nThe pod description shows:\n- `/etc/health` mounted from `health-user-password` secret (ro)\n- `/etc/health/overrides` mounted from `health-overrides` ConfigMap (ro)\n- `/usr/local/bin/health-check.sh` mounted from `health-check-script` ConfigMap (ro)\n\nThe key clue: \"SCRAM authentication failed, storedKey mismatch\" - the health-user password in the secret doesn't match what's stored in MongoDB on pod 1. But pods 0 and 2 pass the health check. This suggests the health check is using a different password than what's configured on pod 1's MongoDB instance.\n\nI need to examine the health-check script, the health-user-password secret, and the health-overrides configmap to see what user and password combination is being used on each pod.\n\nThe storedKey mismatch means the SCRAM authentication failed at password verification - the secret's password doesn't match what's in MongoDB's user database on pod 1. Since this is a replica set with auth enabled, all three members should share the same user database, so if pods 0 and 2 work fine, pod 1 should too unless it has out-of-sync data or the user was created differently. The \"overrides\" configmap is suspicious - there might be a per-pod override with an incorrect password.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8932,"cache_read_input_tokens":29535,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8932},"output_tokens":19,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"081357a4-f7f7-48b0-8327-f42d73a33d23","uuid":"93d0da39-dfe1-4eb2-b975-de7564c40a72","request_id":"req_011CbyK7YV41mRfjA8spxyQe"}
