{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LnWRfggk8sgoy8LQ5ZCAPa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The secret is mounted with an explicit `items` mapping:\n```yaml\nitems:\n- key: password\n  path: health-password\n```\n\nSo the secret key `password` is mapped to the path `health-password`, resulting in the file `/etc/health/health-password`. This explains why pods 0 and 2 work - they read `/etc/health/health-password` which contains `healthpass123`.\n\nNow the issue is clear:\n- The `health-overrides` ConfigMap has `mongodb-replica-1: legacyHealthPass123`\n- Pod 1 reads this override instead of the correct password file\n- The actual MongoDB `health-user` password is `healthpass123`, so `legacyHealthPass123` fails authentication\n\nThe fix is to remove the `mongodb-replica-1` key from the `health-overrides` ConfigMap so pod 1 falls back to reading the correct password from the mounted secret.\n\nI should also check the replica set status to confirm pod 1 is actually part of the RS and there's no other underlying issue.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":766,"cache_read_input_tokens":43669,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":766},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"081357a4-f7f7-48b0-8327-f42d73a33d23","uuid":"083cb75c-49c1-47fc-b8d7-126dfdfa7f91","request_id":"req_011CbyKDVTuTHi6sVRrQBzGy"}
