{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0199HG9zApW3Q8xV6sRxLeBs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The replica set is fully healthy. Here's a summary of what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** The `health-overrides` ConfigMap had a stale entry `mongodb-replica-1: legacyHealthPass123`. The health check script on pod 1 read this override file instead of the real password (`healthpass123` from the secret), causing SCRAM authentication to fail with \"storedKey mismatch\".\n\n**Fix:** Removed the `mongodb-replica-1` key from the `health-overrides` ConfigMap. Pod 1 restarted (liveness probe had also fired), then came back up reading the correct password from `/etc/health/health-password`.\n\n**Current state:**\n- All 3 pods: `1/1 Ready`\n- `mongodb-replica-0` → PRIMARY\n- `mongodb-replica-1` → SECONDARY  \n- `mongodb-replica-2` → SECONDARY"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":479,"cache_read_input_tokens":54556,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":479},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"081357a4-f7f7-48b0-8327-f42d73a33d23","uuid":"b4e6240d-2894-4cb3-bb97-ed268e70eab2","request_id":"req_011CbyKf2RBb2tkhaFKaoQLy"}
